$ SAS macros: sql related

{ Selecting one column

  { From a Dataset

    gh|about-SAS|/macros/sql/Sel1Col/dataset.sas||

    { Testing:

      The following example creates a dataset and the uses `%tq84_sqlDataSetSel1Col` to select the
      variable names from → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/dictionary/columns[dictionary.columns] and
      then, it selects the values of `col_one` from the created data set.

      gh|about-SAS|/macros/sql/Sel1Col/tests/dataset.sas||

    }


  }

  { From a DBMS

    gh|about-SAS|/macros/sql/Sel1Col/dbms.sas||

    The following test uses `%tq84_sqlDBMSSel1Col_F` to select Oracle table names from all_tables. With → Companies-Products/SAS/macros/array[%tq84_array], the result
    is converted into a macro array.

    gh|about-SAS|/macros/sql/Sel1Col/tests/dbms.sas||

    

  }

